<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Blot1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Blot,</orth> subst., 1) a spot or stain on paper: <cit><quote>nature, drawing of an antick, made a foul b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 64</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with inky --s and rotten parchment bonds,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 64</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) anything disfiguring: <cit><quote>worse than a slavish wipe or birth-hour's b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 537" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 537</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the --s of Nature's hand,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.416" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 416</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>full of unpleasing --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 45</bibl></cit>.
<lb />Especially in a moral sense, == stain, disgrace, reproach: <bibl n="shak. luc 1322" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1322</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 36.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 36, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.92.13" default="NO" valid="yes">92, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.95.11" default="NO" valid="yes">95, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. V, 4, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.114" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.325" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 325</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.162" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 162</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.116" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.234" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 234</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.230" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 230</bibl>. <cit><quote>time hath set a b. upon my pride,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.81" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 81</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>marked with a b., damned in the book of heaven,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.236.81" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 236</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>